    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**33.1 E2 1D Boundary Value Problem, System of Equations**

<p>Let \( y = y(x) \) be a solution to the boundary value problem:</p>

<p>
  \(\displaystyle {@p(x)*'diff('y,x,2) + q(x)*'diff('y,x) + r(x)*'y(x) = s(x)@} \quad 0 < x < {@L@} \)
</p>
<p>
  \( y(0) = {@y0@} \), \( y({@L@}) = {@yL@} \)
</p>

<p>
Using a mesh width of \( h = {@h@} \), obtain a central difference approximation to the differential equation and hence find a system of equations satisfied by \( y_1 \approx y({@h@}) \), \( y_2 \approx y({@2*h@}) \), and \( y_3 \approx y({@3*h@}) \). </p>

<p>Specify the values to 3 d.p. (trailing zeros can be ommitted).
</p>

<table border="0">
 <tbody>
  <tr>
   <td>[[input:S_A]]</td>
   <td>[[validation:S_A]]</td>
   <td>\( \left[ \begin{array}{c} y_1 \\ y_2 \\ y_3 \end{array} \right] = \) </td>
   <td>[[input:S_b]]</td>
   <td>[[validation:S_b]]</td>
  </tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<p>[[feedback:GLS]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
